# Every docker/*/Dockerfile that builds from source does `COPY . .` from the
# repository root. Host-side CMake build directories (created by ci.yml or
# any local `cmake -B build`) bake the host's absolute source path into
# CMakeCache.txt; if one of these directories is copied into an image build
# context, the container's own `cmake -B build` step refuses to reconfigure
# ("The source ... does not match the source ... used to generate cache")
# because /src (the container's checkout path) doesn't match the host path
# recorded in the stale cache. Mirrors the CMake-artifact entries in
# .gitignore — vcpkg_installed/ is deliberately NOT excluded here, since
# poco_discovery_node's Dockerfile (and others) rely on COPY . . bringing in
# already-built vcpkg packages rather than re-bootstrapping vcpkg in-image.
build/
build-fmt/
build-coverage/
cmake-build-*/
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
cmake_install.cmake
Testing/
CTestTestfile.cmake
test_results/

.git/
